---
description: Backend architecture rules
globs: ["apps/api/**"]
---
- Flow: Controller → Manager → Service → Repository. Adapters wrap external SDKs.
- Controllers: HTTP binding only, exactly one manager call, no logic/SDK/env/repository access.
- Managers orchestrate services; never touch DB/SDK/HTTP directly.
- Services: one focused capability, small methods, no raw SDK, no process.env.
- Only `GeminiAdapter` may import the Gemini SDK. Only config module reads process.env.
- Map all errors to DomainException; never leak provider errors or stack traces.
